<poem>
<coder>TL</coder>
<header>
    <title>>The Day Breakers</title>
    <byLine poet="Bontemps_A">Arna Bontemps</byLine>
</header>
<content>
<line n="1" stanza="1">We are not come to wage a strife </line>
<line n="2" stanza="1">With swords upon this hill<punc type="comma">,</punc> </line>
<line n="3" stanza="1">It is not wise to waste the life </line>
<line n="4" stanza="1">Against a stubborn will<punc type="period">.</punc> </line>
<line n="5" stanza="1">Yet would we die as some have done<punc type="period">.</punc> </line>
<line n="6" stanza="1">Beating a way for the rising sun<punc type="period">.</punc></line>
</content>
</poem>